***************** {FM.js(engine);} *****************

{FM.js(engine);} is a free and open source 2D game engine for HTML5 developers.
Entirely written in JavaScript it allows you to build your games and prototypes quickly.
It runs on every modern browser and does not rely on any external libraries such as jQuery or Prototype.

How to:

- Just modify the "FMHelloWorld" project that you can find in my repositories here on GitHub and start your game. 
- The "index.html" file features the name of your game as well as the JS files that must be included. 
- The "ExampleProject.js" file is the starting point of your game, just modify the name of the file and there 
you can add assets and choose the screen resolution.
- Documentation will be available soon.

Features:

- Keyboard and mouse input management
- Game states management
- Camera management (viewport, scrolling, culling)
- Types affectation (create group)
- Simple physics with AABB and circles
- Orthogonal tiles management
- Import from tmx files (Tiled Map Editor))
- Texts, sprites and animated sprites management
- Particles!
- Simple pathfinding system
- Assets preloading (custom preloader)
- Debug information

Future work:

- Quadtree for collision detection
- Input management for touch devices
- Isometric tiles management
- OBB physics
